HEADWORD: Munchausenism
<hw>Mun*chau"sen*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called in
allusion to <person>Baron <ets>Munchausen's</ets></person> extravagant
tales of travel.]</ety> <def>An extravagant fiction embodying an account
of some marvelous exploit or adventure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muncher</ent>⟦br⟧
